<item>
            <title>[LU-5882] Conflict in exported symbols, clients cannot load modules</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5882</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Modprobe fails on all Lustre clients&lt;br/&gt;
WARNING: Error inserting obdclass (/lib/modules/2.6.32-431.29.2.el6.x86_64/extra/kernel/fs/lustre/obdclass.ko): Invalid module format&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Syslog reports duplicate symbol&lt;br/&gt;
obdclass: exports duplicate symbol obd_memory (owned by lvfs)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;# objdump --sym /lib/modules/2.6.32-431.29.2.el6.x86_64/weak-updates/kernel/fs/lustre/lvfs.ko |grep obd_memory
0000000000000050 l     O __ksymtab      0000000000000010 __ksymtab_obd_memory
0000000000000043 l     O __ksymtab_strings      000000000000000b __kstrtab_obd_memory
0000000000000028 l     O __kcrctab      0000000000000008 __kcrctab_obd_memory
0000000000000000 g     O .bss   0000000000000008 obd_memory
000000007562dcf8 g       *ABS*  0000000000000000 __crc_obd_memory
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
